                }
            ],
            "subtype": "sidebar",
            "sidebar_type": "related_creatures",
            "sidebar_heading": "Related Creatures",
            "image": {
                "type": "image",
                "name": "Related Creatures",
                "image": "Sidebar_4_RelatedCreatures.png"
            },
            "html": "Other varieties of bebaki flit amid the jungle canopies of the Mwangi Expanse, their relationship to one another identifiable by the constant feature of their massive and deadly tail feathers. A subspecies called long-beaked emperor birds is remarkable for its bright yellow plumage and its namesake beak, which is long and sharp enough to dig through ironwood tree trunks, allowing it to feast on the golden sting ants native to certain corners of the Mwangi Expanse."
        }
    ],
